str2: From sun and the base of tribos; to crush completely, i.e. To shatter.
A reed; a reed-pen, reed-staff, measuring rod. Or uncertain affinity; a reed; by implication, a pen.

parse: Verb - Future Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To break down (in pieces), crush, break into. From kata and the base of rhegnumi; to rend in pieces, i.e. Crack apart.

parse: Verb - Present Participle Middle or Passive - Accusative Neuter Singular
str2: To raise smoke, smolder. Apparently a primary verb; to make a smoke, i.e. Slowly consume without flame.
Flax, linen. Probably a primary word; flax, i.e. 'linen'.

parse: Verb - Future Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: (a) I extinguish, quench, (b) I suppress, thwart. A prolonged form of an apparently primary verb; to extinguish.
A conjunction, preposition and adverb of continuance, until.

parse: Verb - Aorist Subjunctive Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To throw (cast, put) out; I banish; I bring forth, produce. From ek and ballo; to eject.
Decision; by extension, a tribunal; by implication, justice.
A primary preposition; to or into, of place, time, or purpose; also in adverbial phrases.
Victory. From nike; a conquest, i.e. triumph.
